/-!
# LMFDB level-1 modular form orbit `1.68.a.{a..}` (Hecke field degree 5)

The Hecke field `K = ℚ(α)` is degree 5 over ℚ. The LMFDB lists q-coefficients as
elements of `K`, which we decompose as `c_0 + c_1 · α + … + c_{4} · α^4`.
The combined form is `f = f_0 + α · f_1 + … + α^4 · f_{4}`, with each
`f_j` a level-1 weight-68 form with rational coefficients in `(E₄, E₆)`.

The Sturm bound for weight 68 is `⌊68/12⌋ + 1 = 6`. After certifying agreement
on the first 6 q-coefficients, `ModularForm.eq_of_sturm_bound` lets us conclude that any
form with the same coefficients equals our explicit `lmfdb_1_68_a_orbit`.

Generated by `scripts/lmfdb_qexp_to_e4e6_v3.sage`.
-/

