/-! ## Uniqueness theorem -/


/-- **Uniqueness theorem.** Any level-1 weight-68 modular form `f` whose first 6
q-coefficients match the LMFDB-published values for `1.68.a.{a..}` is equal to our
explicit construction `lmfdb_1_68_a_orbit`. Proven via `ModularForm.eq_of_sturm_bound`. -/
theorem identifies_lmfdb_1_68_a_orbit (f : ModularForm 𝒮ℒ 68)
    (h_0 : (PowerSeries.coeff (R := ℂ) 0) (qExpansion 1 (f : ℍ → ℂ)) = 0)
